erOn, we record your WaterOn model and serial number, software version, and technical information such as battery charge level.<br><br><b>What information is shared among multiple connected SmarterHomes Products?<br></b>If you have multiple SmarterHomes Products interfacing with one another, the products will share certain information with each other, such as occupancy data on whether someone is using the property. This sharing may occur locally among connected devices (both SmarterHomes and third-party devices). Sharing can also occur between SmarterHomes Products and your mobile device or application, or among SmarterHomes's servers. <br><br><b>What additional information does SmarterHomes collect and store when a user connects a SmarterHomes Product to the Internet or creates an account?<br></b>Only applicable to WaterOn WOW WiFi model - Wi-Fi Network Information: To connect your SmarterHomes Product to our Services, or to access your SmarterHomes Product over the Internet from a computer, a smartphone or a tablet, you will need to connect it to your Wi-Fi network (applicable only for the WiFI variant). During setup, the SmarterHomes Product will ask for your Wi-Fi network name (SSID) and password to connect to the Internet. It will save this information on the device, along with your IP address, so that you can access it and control it from your computer, smartphone or tablet, and so that it can communicate with SmarterHomes servers and download software updates.<br><br>Once connected to your Wi-Fi network, your SmarterHomes Product regularly sends the data described in this Privacy Statement (excluding your Wi-Fi password) to SmarterHomes to provide you with the Services.<br>Additional authorised Users: SmarterHomes may provide you with the ability to enable additional authorised users to access your account. If you do so, the additional authorised users may control and view all of your devices, content. Invited users may also add additional authorised users to