ations about products, safety, or energy use. We may use your contact details to send you this information, or to ask you to participate in surveys about your SmarterHomes use, and to send you other communications from SmarterHomes.<br><br>We may also use this information in an aggregated, non-identified form for research purposes and to help us make sales, marketing, and business decisions. For example, we use aggregated user information about the number of active meter connections and their consumption to use in the case studies and other marketing collaterals. We never use any personally identifiable data in any such case studies or marketing collaterals.<br><br>We may use service providers to perform some of these functions. Those service providers are restricted from sharing your information for any other purpose.<br><br>We use industry-standard methods to keep this information safe and secure while it is transmitted over your home network and through the Internet to our servers. Depending on your location and type of data, SmarterHomes may process your personal information on servers that are not in your home country.<br>In what circumstances does SmarterHomes share my information?<br><br>Under no circumstance do we share personal information for any commercial or marketing purpose unrelated to the activation and delivery of SmarterHomes Products and services without asking you first. Period. We do not rent or sell our customer lists.<br><br>The following are the limited situations where we may share personal information:<br>With your explicit consent: We may share personal information when we have your consent. One example of this would be if you invite another user to access the Products on your account as an additional authorised user. <br><br>For external processing: We have vendors, service providers, and technicians who help with some of our processing and storage, including helping to answer your questions. They may also assist with monitoring our servers for technical problems. <br><br> These technicians (as well as SmarterHomes employees) can access certain information about you or your account in line with this work but these technicians are not allowed to use this data for non-SmarterHomes purposes. We also have strict policies and technical barriers in place to prevent unauthorised employee access to video data.<br>As part of business transitions: Upon the sale or transfer of the company and/or all or part of its assets, your personal information may be among the items sold or transferred. We will request a purchaser to treat our data under the privacy statement in place at the time of its collection.<br><br>For legal reasons: We may provide information to a third party if we believe in good faith that we are required to do so for legal reasons. For example, to respond to legal process, or comply with state and penal laws (or the applicable laws of foreign countries other than the United States).&nbsp;We may share non-personal information (for example, aggregated or anonymised customer data) publicly and with our partners. <br><br><b>Support/ticket related data</b><br>SmarterHomes will ensure complete safety and protection of end user data acquired through various support channels and will not share this with any other party without the explicit written consent from the customer. In the event of such consent, SmarterHomes will be absolved of any liability arising due to misuse of personally identifiable information.<br><br> <b>How long does SmarterHomes save my personal information.</b><br>SmarterHomes generally stores your personal information on SmarterHomes’s servers until you delete or edit it, or for as long as you remain a SmarterHomes customer in order to provide you with SmarterHomes Products.<br>As described above, some information is processed and stored directly on the SmarterHomes device. All personal information is encrypted as it is transmitted to SmarterHomes and cannot easily be accessed.<br>P